cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with the extraction of curve skeleton from unorganized point cloud, which is a fundamental task of computer vision. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper involves the construction of a tree-structured point cloud dataset and the use of mesh models, which are related to graphics. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper discusses the use of different methods to build four different types of point cloud models, which can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper mentions the evaluation of skeleton extraction algorithms, which can involve the use of machine learning techniques. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper involves the use of virtual scanner for the sampling of point cloud, which can be related to multimedia.
